enters the incomplete side only through the phase u = r mod q (E_S is
a function of the phase vector and g).  The bridge (T1c, validated at
every prime above) maps a circle frequency u to the complete diagonal
Kloosterman sum: circleSum_q(u) = -kloos_q(u*inv2, u*inv2).  The most
natural complete-sum comparand at clock q is therefore
  K_q(W) = kloos_q(u*inv2_q, u*inv2_q),  u = r mod q,
